cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on sequence labelling in Natural Language Processing (NLP) and proposes a method to improve it using linguistic features. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed method involves adding features to a neural sequence framework to improve performance. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of NLP tasks using machine learning techniques. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper involves the use of neural networks to improve sequence labelling. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with image or video data, but the proposed method of adding selective readings of character embeddings could be seen as a form of feature extraction similar to computer vision tasks.
